Apparently its masks optional for the waiters, waitresses, bartenders and management at The Industry. I made a reservation for outdoor dining to support a local restaurant that I frequented pre-covid, and ordered take out from in the midst of quarantine.  This is my first time dining at a restaurant since the ban was lifted in phase II of the re-opening, however had talked to friends who had good experiences at other restaurants, so figured it was time.  After being seated, our waitress came to our table to take our drink order and had her mask on her chin, exposing both her nose and mouth.  I didn't say anything figuring she probably just forgot. When she came back with our drinks, she still had her mask in the same spot, so I nicely asked if she wouldn't mind covering her face to which she was not pleased with my question. The dining experience only worsened from there. She had an attitude the entire time, barely checked on us, and brought out everyone's meal but mine -- I had to flag her down and ask for it 5 minutes later.  After dining, I went inside and asked to speak to the manager. I was introduced to a man wearing a mask only covering his mouth. I explained to him the situation, and he responded by saying how they are following all safety procedures and what did I want? I informed him that I only wanted him to have his staff wear masks, and he said who isn't? Well for starters, you -- your bartender behind you and majority of your wait staff including my waitress. He was unhelpful and rude. I went back outside, asked the only waitress wearing a mask for my bill, paid, and went back inside to ask for the Manager's business card.  When I asked him for his card, he went in the back to only come out saying he didn't have one. I asked for his name and number and he asked "why" -- he told me I was disrupting all his patrons, and upsetting his wait staff. I never raised my voice, and the only thing I asked for was his business card.  His name is David, or that's the fake name he wrote on a piece of receipt paper.  I understand restaurants are experiencing a difficult time, hence why I am supporting them.  Never did I ask for money off my bill, I simply asked for the staff to wear a mask to keep the patron's safe.  Is that wrong? Is that too much to ask?  I hate to do this, but I would not recommend going to this restaurant in the midst of the pandemic.

A new addition to Adams Village in Dorchester, Industry on Adams (at the site of what was Sonny's) offers a fresh take on the dining experience.  Over sixty types of scotch, menu items created by Executive Chef Steven Coe,  with events such as their upcoming New Years Eve dinner and others.  Brunch menu offered, as is valet parking after 5pm.  See the Milton Insider app to tap into the website to everything about this Adams Street hit!

Staff food and drinks excellent. Prices are little higher but worth it will go back when I want something a little nicer than the neighborhood pub.

Appetizer- cheese assortment was delicious but ask for extra crackers...    Filet mignon was excellent.  Dessert- large bowl-2 scoops of taramezoo gelato. Coffee was delicious but could be hotter.  Dinner total time 2 hours, not rushed at all. Three of us for dinner. Waite staff was wonderful... Met several neighbor's who stopped and chatted at our table.  Nice ambiance. Pricing higher than other neighborhood eateries, but would go again, but not every week.  Nice addition to the neighborhood.  I do miss the prices and food of the previous restaurant-. Sonny's- but I know times are changing and it is good that improvements are made to the building and area....... I would highly recommend this restaurant!

Loved the presentation!  Great Calamari which is better than Lucy's and certainly true of the Landmark Public House, both are just up the street, and Dorset's as well.  The Industry is more in line with what I expect in terms of ambiance, quality, quantity, and customer service.  Prices are a bit high for the neighborhood, but not overly so.  I like having  an upscale restaurant in the area, just a few blocks from home.
